c: 12
v: 66
t: "He said: \"Never will I send him with you until you give me a solemn pledge in God’s Name that you will indeed bring him back to me, unless you are (in some insurmountable way) overwhelmed. Then, when they gave him their solemn pledge, he said: \"God is witness to and watcher over all that we say (and only on Him can we rely to fulfill our pledges)"